verses.text_plain: And the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Son of man, What is the vine tree more than any tree, or than a branch which is among the trees of the forest?
verses.verse_html: 2Son of man, What is the vine tree more than any tree, or than a branch which is among the trees of the forest?

verses.text_plain: Shall wood be taken thereof to do any work? or will men take a pin of it to hang any vessel thereon?
verses.verse_html: 3Shall wood be taken thereof to do any work? or will men take a pin of it to hang any vessel thereon?

verses.text_plain: Behold, it is cast into the fire for fuel; the fire devoureth both the ends of it, and the midst of it is burned. Is it meet for any work?
verses.verse_html:
4Behold, it is cast into the fire for fuel; the fire devoureth both the ends of it, and the midst of it is burned. Is it meet for any work? ▼
▼ Is it…: Heb. Will it prosper?

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Is it…: Heb. Will it prosper?
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Is it…: Heb. Will it prosper?

verses.text_plain: Behold, when it was whole, it was meet for no work: how much less shall it be meet yet for any work, when the fire hath devoured it, and it is burned?
verses.verse_html:
5Behold, when it was whole, it was meet for no work: how much less shall it be meet yet for any work, when the fire hath devoured it, and it is burned? ▼
▼ meet: Heb. made fit

tokens.text: how much less shall it be meet

footnotes.body_html: ▼ meet: Heb. made fit

verses.text_plain: Therefore thus saith the Lord God; As the vine tree among the trees of the forest, which I have given to the fire for fuel, so will I give the inhabitants of Jerusalem.
verses.verse_html: 6Therefore thus saith the Lord God; As the vine tree among the trees of the forest, which I have given to the fire for fuel, so will I give the inhabitants of Jerusalem.

verses.text_plain: And I will set my face against them; they shall go out from one fire, and another fire shall devour them; and ye shall know that I am the Lord, when I set my face against them.
verses.verse_html: 7And I will set my face against them; they shall go out from one fire, and another fire shall devour them; and ye shall know that I am the Lord, when I set my face against them.

tokens.text: against them; they shall go out

verses.text_plain: And I will make the land desolate, because they have committed a trespass, saith the Lord God.
verses.verse_html:
8And I will make the land desolate, because they have committed a trespass, saith the Lord God. ▼
▼ committed…: Heb. trespassed a trespass

footnotes.body_html: ▼ committed…: Heb. trespassed a trespass
